1 Setup
http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/cli-chap-getting-set-up.html

$ sudo easy_install pip
  or
$ sudo apt-get install python-pip
  or
$ sudo yum install python-pip
  then
$sudo pip install awscli

2. Configure
http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/cli-chap-getting-started.html

$ cat ~/.aws/config
[default]
aws_access_key_id = AKIAJBIQPTWOULGJSABQ
aws_secret_access_key = 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
region = us-west-2

To enable tab completion for bash, use the built-in command complete:

$ complete -C aws_completer aws
(need to put in .bashrc if you dont want to do this every session!)

3. Command Referenc:
http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/
